While performing and analysing the Paballo Hospital project here is my Project Findings :


Analyzed hospital patient records to understand patient admissions, billing, diagnoses, doctor performance, and bed occupancy.

Found that viral infections accounted for the highest number of patient admissions, while fractures had the lowest number of cases during the analysis period.

Private hospital rooms were the most occupied, showing a higher preference compared to general and ICU beds.

Billing amounts varied across different diagnoses, helping identify treatments that generated higher hospital revenue.

Doctor feedback scores remained consistently good, indicating a satisfactory patient experience across the hospital.

Health insurance covered a significant portion of the treatment costs, reducing the financial burden on many patients.

Different medical tests showed different billing patterns, helping identify the most frequently performed and higher-cost tests.

The interactive dashboard made it easy to track patient trends, hospital revenue, diagnosis patterns, doctor performance, and bed occupancy, supporting better hospital planning and decision-making.
